verse_part: are you doing on the road
are you doing on the road
In the time of her heat
you will be put to shame
And you have had your way
as of a woman in labor
as of one giving birth to her first child
as of a woman in childbirth
Then I will make to cease
You will bring me to nothing
And let us cut him off
and they have tired you out,
I have come to hate her
and I will bring them back
so as not to destroy them
They have been put to shame
am going to make an end
although it was not I who sent
are the one who has done
I will bereave them of children
to you, But as for you, you must not turn
and they will fish for them;
am going to make them know
And I will make you serve
but as for me, let me not be put
but let me not be dismayed
and let us strike at him
and I will cause them to fall
and he will carry them away as exiles
so that the enemy will withdraw
and he will strike them down
the one who has been robbed
for the one who goes away;
Is not that what it means to know
and I will give you over
And would have turned them back
and I will bring them again
and I will build them up
you might provoke Me to anger
and I will utterly destroy them
Then I will bring them back
I will also bring them back
shall be one of them, And their ruler
and she who is in labor with child,
will you go here and there
so that it should be removed
and I will bring them back
and will have mercy on them
and I will bring them back
to them--but they did not listen
for they had not yet put
and one of the chief officers
so that he will have compassion
for it is you who sent
and I am going to set
so as to provoke Me to anger
them and did not all this come
It will even be burned down
and let us cut her off
and they will tip him over
you shake your head in scorn
and the one who burns incense
And the one who climbs up
I will make him run away
They have made them turn aside
and they will be dried up!
I will make them run away
